1. *Ališe* mi se svako jutro kada se probudim. (I have bags under my eyes every morning when I wake up.)
2. Kada sam videla taj film, *alisa* mi je stala. (When I saw that movie, my breath was taken away.)
3. Uradila sam to *na aliski način*. (I did it in a haphazard way.)
4. Nisam sigurna da li će *ališ* na mojoj glavi da me smeta tokom puta. (I'm not sure if my fringe will bother me on the trip.)
5. Trenutno *ne mogu da vidim alis svoje kose* zbog maske za lice. (I currently can't see my hairline because of my face mask.)
6. Ona je *odsekla alise* pre nekoliko dana i sada joj kosa izgleda mnogo drugačije. (She cut her bangs a few days ago and now her hair looks very different.)
7. *Na aliski način* se obukla za tu proslavu, ali nije shvatila da je dress code bio crni tie. (She dressed haphazardly for that party, but didn't realize that the dress code was black tie.)
8. Moram da se podsetim da obrišem *prašinu sa alise* u hodniku. (I need to remember to dust the coat rack in the hallway.)

(Note: "alis" in Serbian refers to bangs or fringe in English, but it can also be used in some idiomatic expressions, such as "na aliski način" which means haphazardly or without order.)